{"title_page": "Renan Brito Soares", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Renan\n| image = Renan-XerezCD-p1040365.jpg\n| fullname = Renan Brito Soares\n| height = 1.85 m\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1985|1|24|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Viam\u00e3o]], Brazil \n| currentclub  = [[Clube Esportivo Bento Gon\u00e7alves|Bento Gon\u00e7alves]]\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1 = 2004\u20132005\n| youthclubs1 = [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]]\n| years1 = 2005\u20132008 | clubs1 = [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]] | caps1 = 33 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2008\u20132011 | clubs2 = [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] | caps2 = 19 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Xerez CD|Xerez]] (loan) | caps3 = 35 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2010\u20132011 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]] (loan) | caps4 = 27 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2011\u20132012 | clubs5 = [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]] | caps5 = 1 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2013\u20132017 | clubs6 = [[Goi\u00e1s Esporte Clube|Goi\u00e1s]] | caps6 = 122 | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2018      | clubs7 = [[Cear\u00e1 Sporting Club|Cear\u00e1]] | caps7 = 0   | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 2019      | clubs8 = [[Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento|S\u00e3o Bento]] | caps8 = 0   | goals8 = 0\n| years9 = 2020\u2013     | clubs9 = [[Clube Esportivo Bento Gon\u00e7alves|Bento Gon\u00e7alves]] | caps9 = 0   | goals9 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2008\n| nationalteam1 = [[Brazil Olympic football team|Brazil U23]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 8\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate = 14:51, 17 October 2015 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = 26 June 2012\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry|{{flagu|Brazil}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[Football at the Summer Olympics|Football]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2008 Summer Olympics|2008 Beijing]]|[[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Team Competition]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Renan Brito Soares''' or simply '''Renan'''  (born 24 January 1985 in [[Viam\u00e3o]]) is a Brazilian [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Clube Esportivo Bento Gon\u00e7alves|Bento Gon\u00e7alves]].\n\n== Career ==\nRenan made his professional debut for [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]] against [[Esporte Clube Juventude|Juventude]] in the [[Campeonato Ga\u00facho|Rio Grande do Sul State League]] in a 1\u20130 win on April 3, 2005.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://internacional.com.br/jogadorescolorados/?codigo=60 |title=Site oficial do Sport Club Internacional de Porto Alegre |access-date=June 5, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303193104/http://internacional.com.br/jogadorescolorados/?codigo=60 |archive-date=March 3, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Valencia===\nRenan joined Spanish club [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] on 13 August 2008.<ref name=\"valenciaofspai\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gazetaesportiva.net/ge_noticias/bin/noticia.php?chid=114&nwid=283204|title=Inter confirma e Renan vai para o Val\u00eancia|publisher=Gazeta Esportiva|accessdate=August 11, 2008|date=August 11, 2008|language=Portuguese}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> He made his debut for [[Valencia CF]] in a 3\u20130 win against [[Real Mallorca]]. He made a great start to his [[Valencia CF]] career and was their number one keeper, but on 20 January 2009 he sustained a groin injury in a match against [[Athletic de Bilbao]] and was ruled out for six weeks, enabling veteran [[C\u00e9sar S\u00e1nchez]] to step in. After recovering from his injury he remained on the bench till the end of the 2008\u201309 season owing to Cesar's fine form, and following the close season signing of [[Miguel \u00c1ngel Moy\u00e0]] from [[Real Mallorca]] he left the [[Mestalla]].\n\n===Xerez===\n[[Xerez CD|Xerez]] signed the Brazilian goalkeeper on loan from [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] on 27 July 2009.<ref>[http://www.trivela.com/Noticias.aspx?view=FqdC1nihoDQ=&id=28984 Valencia empresta goleiro Renan ao Xerez] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090804150052/http://www.trivela.com/Noticias.aspx?view=FqdC1nihoDQ= |date=August 4, 2009 }}</ref>\n\n===Internacional===\nOn 4 June 2010, [[Sport Club Internacional]] signed him on loan from [[Valencia CF|Valencia]].<ref>[http://esportes.terra.com.br/futebol/brasileiro/2010/noticias/0,,OI4467511-EI15406,00.html Goleiro Renan acerta retorno ao Internacional, diz jornal]</ref>\n\nOn 13 December 2018, Renan joined [[Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie B]] side [[Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento|S\u00e3o Bento]] on a one-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecsaobento.com.br/site/news.php?page=1&id=1028&t=S%C3%A3o_Bento_anuncia_contrata%C3%A7%C3%A3o_de_goleiro_Renan_e_lateral_Guilherme_Rom%C3%A3o|title=S\u00e3o Bento anuncia contrata\u00e7\u00e3o de goleiro Renan e lateral Guilherme Rom\u00e3o|publisher=[[Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento]]|date=13 December 2018|accessdate=14 December 2018|language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nRenan was a member of [[Brazil Olympic football team|Brazil]]'s team for the [[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics|2008 Summer Olympics]], he was the first-choice goalkeeper for the tournament, appearing in all matches as Brazil went on to get the bronze medal.\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n;Internacional\n* [[Campeonato Ga\u00facho|Rio Grande do Sul State League]]: 2005, 2008, 2011, 2012\n* [[Copa Libertadores]]: [[2006 Copa Libertadores|2006]], [[2010 Copa Libertadores|2010]]\n* [[FIFA Club World Cup]]: [[2006 FIFA Club World Cup|2006]]\n* [[Recopa Sudamericana]]: [[2007 Recopa Sudamericana|2007]], [[2011 Recopa Sudamericana|2011]]\n\n;Goi\u00e1s\n* [[Campeonato Goiano|Goi\u00e1s State League]]: 2013\n\n===International===\n;Brazil\n* [[2008 Beijing Summer Olympics|2008 Summer Olympics]]: Bronze medal winner\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{BDFutbol|8476|